cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.RO 

This paper proposes a new approach to population sizing for memetic algorithms, which are commonly used in optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves designing an algorithm and tuning coefficients, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves measuring the performance of the algorithm, which suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper applies the proposed approach to a specific problem, the multidimensional assignment problem, which suggests the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics).
